            . I keep the <placeName id="t18291029-205-crimeloc1161">Bacchus, public-house at Hoxton</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-205-crimeloc1161" type="placeName" value="Bacchus, public-house at Hoxton"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-205-crimeloc1161" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-205-off1159 t18291029-205-crimeloc1161"></join>. I was in the <placeName id="t18291029-205-crimeloc1162">skittle-ground</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-205-crimeloc1162" type="placeName" value="skittle-ground"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-205-crimeloc1162" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-205-off1159 t18291029-205-crimeloc1162"></join> about five or six weeks back; Mr. Collins had been there two or three times; and that day he pulled off his coat and hat, left them in the Dutchpin box, and went into another ground; I heard a person had come over the wall; I went out and saw the prisoner; he gave these things into my arms and ran away; I had known him very well by his coming to the ground.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. What time was it? A. From half-past five to half-past six o'clock; it was between the lights - you threw the things into my arms - I did not stay three seconds; you are the person who gave them to me - I took them back to Mr. Collins; I did not see you again till you were at the office - it might be four or five weeks afterwards.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-205-person1697">
                  JAMES 
                  COLLINS
               <interp inst="t18291029-205-person1697" type="surname" value="COLLINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-205-person1697" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-205-person1697" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at the skittle-ground on the 14th of October, and took off my coat and hat in the Dutchpin ground - I went to another ground, and heard a person drop off the wall on the other side; I looked, and missed my things - I had not seen the prisoner then, but Barker gave me my things; the coat had the pocket-book and snuff-box in the pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-205-person1698">
                  JOHN 
                  FRYER
               <interp inst="t18291029-205-person1698" type="surname" value="FRYER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-205-person1698" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-205-person1698" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was described to me; I found him on the 15th of October in Hoxton - he ran away, and was stopped by another person; when I came up, he said, "Do you want me for the Bacchus job?" I said Yes.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I believe another officer can prove to the contrary; I never was in the skittle-ground that night - do you think, when he saw me only three seconds, and did not see me again for five weeks, he could know me again.?</p>
               <p>
